Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance of V2X communication using different radio access technologies. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the transmission of data packets and the use of diversity gain. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a multi-RATs scheme to improve the system performance. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of different interfaces to enable V2X communication. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also less likely but possible as the paper briefly mentions the requirement for ultra-high reliability in V2X communication.
